title: Library. University of Idaho. ca. 1900

title: Mary Belle Sweet
description: M. Belle Sweet, in later years, University of Idaho's first professional librarian.

title: Gym
description: Bookcases take a backseat to athletics in this 1907 photo showing the library's collection, far left, housed in the gymnasium's wings.
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library. #1-54-06

title: Prank article from the Argonaut
description: Article features a photo of multi-storey office tower in downtown Spokane as image of 'The New Library'

title: Loan desk
description: Students checking out books in 1936, while student clerks sort books behind the counter. The library still had 'closed stacks', inaccessible to most students.
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library, #1-201-10

title: The library's second-floor periodicals reading room
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library, #1-201-15

title: Library display
description: Library displays in 1943 featured daily war reports on the 'Pacific Battlefield' and other fronts.
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho, #92-1249a

title: Browsing Room, University of Idaho Library
description: students reading newspapers. Photographer Roy Bell, Photo Services
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library, #1-122-020

title: The Bookmark

source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library, #92-1778a

title: The new library, 1957.
description: The entrance is visible, lower left, just above the stairs. The clock on the exterior wall is just left of where the clocktower / staircase now stands.
source: Historical Photographs Collection, University of Idaho Library, #1-122-001

description: 1967 Argonaut cartoon shows "Library Gestapo" frisking priests at the door. The library had just introduced baggage checks, in response to book thefts.

description: New entrance designed for maximum convenience, Users will find services on the ground floor

title: Library second floor plan
description: The second floor would be devoted almost entirely to periodicals â€” and photocopying. A reading lounge can be seen top-right (next to the bubble lounge). A periodicals services center can be seen in the middle of the floor. On the right side can be seen a photocopying center; and in the bottom-right corner, a classroom for teaching library skills to freshmen. Newspaper and magazine readers will find comfortable areas to sit.
